    <abstract>
      <t>MPLS-SPRING is an MPLS data plane-based source routing paradigm in which a sender of a packet is allowed to partially or completely specify the route the packet takes through the network by imposing stacked MPLS labels to the packet. MPLS-SPRING could be leveraged to realize a unified source routing mechanism across MPLS, IPv4 and IPv6 data planes by using a unified source routing instruction set while preserving backward compatibility with MPLS-SPRING.</t>
